<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-09T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-09T06:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/8–944: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-09T13:00:00+02:00">August 9,
                                    1944—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 9—8:23 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6370. For the Acting Secretary. In regard to second paragraph of your
                            6254 of August 8 I want you to know that the Russians on the European
                            Advisory Commission are not aware that we intend to inform the Chinese
                            in regard to the surrender terms. The conversations within the EAC bind
                            us to absolute secrecy until notice and consent are agreed to by the
                            three parties represented.</p>
                        <p>In relation to this same problem I want to warn you against the Chinese
                            codes which I believe are unsafe and probably known to the Germans as
                            well as to our two Allies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>